# Formatting Style

When generating .md files or text content for this project, keep formatting minimal and clean:

- Avoid excessive markdown decorators. No bold on every heading, no horizontal rules between every section.
- Use plain text headings without bold wrapping (write "Executive Summary" not "**Executive Summary**").
- Use dashes for lists, not asterisks.
- Use em-dashes (—) to separate label from description in list items instead of colons with bold labels.
- Only use tables when the data truly benefits from a grid layout.
- Keep the overall look closer to a clean document than a decorated wiki page.
